A) A UMAP aggregate is shown of all control and DBA EP and MKP cells (n=6380) depicting four distinct subclusters.
plot_umap_label_by_clusters(DBA_MKE,show_method = "merged_louvain",mark.clusters = F)

B) A heatmap is shown for the 15 top differentially expressed genes (row labels, right) for each of the four EP and MKP sub-clusters (color-coded columns).Labels across the top indicate cluster assignment according to their marker genes: early erythroid progenitors (EEP), cycling EP (Ecycling), late erythroid progenitors (LEP) and megakaryocyte progenitors (MKP).
plot_heatmap_for_marker_genes(DBA_MKE,cluster.type = "merged_louvain",isClusterByRow = F,
                              n.TopGenes = 15,min.log2FC = 0.5,min.expFraction = 0.3,
                              rowFont.size = 5,split.line.col = "white")

C) A bubble plot shows the average expression of individual genes (depicted by color) and the fraction of cells expressing that gene (depicted by bubble size) within EP and MKP subclusters from control, RPS-DBA, or RPL-DBA bone marrow. Boxes highlight differentially expressed genes with Log2FC > 0.4 and adjusted P value < 0.05. TF, transcription factor; UMI, unique molecular identifier.
gene.list <- rev(c("GATA2","GATA1","KLF1","FLI1","CD34","TFR2","TFRC","ENG","GYPA","AURKB","MKI67"))


normalized.umi <- get_normalized_umi(DBA_MKE)
cells <- DBA_MKE@umap.result$Cell
normalized.umi <- normalized.umi[gene.list,cells]

umap.results <- DBA_MKE@umap.result
sc.clusters <- DBA_MKE@sc.clusters
umap.results <- umap.results[match(sc.clusters$Cell,umap.results$Cell),]
identical(as.character(umap.results$Cell),as.character(sc.clusters$Cell))  
## [1] TRUE
sc.clusters$genotype <- umap.results$genotype
sc.clusters$type <- paste(sc.clusters$genotype,sc.clusters$merged_louvain,sep = "_")
sc.clusters$subset <- as.numeric(factor(sc.clusters$type))


data <- data.frame()
for (i in 1:length(gene.list)){
  gene <- as.character(gene.list[i])
  expr <- normalized.umi[gene,]
  for (j in 1:12){
    cluster.id = j
    cells <- sc.clusters$Cell[sc.clusters$subset == cluster.id]
    used.expr <- expr[names(expr) %in% cells]
    used.expr <- as.numeric(used.expr)
    n.exp <- length(used.expr[used.expr>0])
    expr.fract <- round(n.exp/length(used.expr) *100)
    expr.mean <- mean(used.expr)
    expr.mean <- log2(expr.mean +1)
    mat <- data.frame(gene =gene,subset = cluster.id, percent = expr.fract, expression = expr.mean)
    data <- rbind(data,mat)
    
  }

}
# data


sc.clusters.used <- sc.clusters[,c("merged_louvain","subset","genotype","type")]
sc.clusters.used <- sc.clusters[!duplicated(sc.clusters.used$type),]

sc.clusters.merged <- merge(data,sc.clusters.used, by.x = "subset",all.x = TRUE)
# sc.clusters.merged



p<- ggplot(sc.clusters.merged,aes(x = type, y = gene, color = expression, size = percent)) +
  geom_point() +
  scale_color_viridis_c(name = 'Log2(mean + 1)',option = "C") +
  scale_x_discrete(limits = c("WT_cl1","RPS_cl1","RPL_cl1","",
                              "WT_cl4","RPS_cl4","RPL_cl4","",
                              "WT_cl3","RPS_cl3","RPL_cl3","",
                              "WT_cl2","RPS_cl2","RPL_cl2")) + 
  theme_classic2() +
  theme(axis.text.x = element_text(angle = 45,vjust = 0.5,hjust = 0.5)) +
  xlab("") +
  ylab("")

p
